> This Coconut Chicken Thigh and Lentil Soup is bursting full of flavours and makes the perfect dinner night option from HelloFresh. Cook up a fresh start!

If you don't have a #toaster{}, heat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7 for the naans.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Once hot, fry the onion and cook, stirring frequently, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @pasanda style seasoning{1%sachet}, lime zest and garlic. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more. Stir in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, lentils, @vegetable stock paste{15%g} and @water for the soup{200%ml} until combined.

Bring the soup to the boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir through the tomato chunks and @baby spinach{40%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the veg has been added to the soup, cut the @plain naans{2} in half widthways, then put in your toaster until golden.

If you're using the oven, put the naans onto a #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with a little water and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When toasted, generously spread the @butter{10%g} over the naans.

Once the soup has thickened slightly, stir through the @mango chutney{40%g} and a squeeze of lime juice.

Season to taste with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lime juice if needed. Remove from the heat.

Share the lentil soup between your #bowls{}.

Serve with the buttery naans alongside. Enjoy!